      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A cold front forms when a colder, denser air mass moves toward a region occupied by warmer, less dense air. Because cold air is heavier, it pushes the warmer air up. This generally leads to a rapid drop in temperature, heavy showers or thunderstorms, and sometimes even severe weather. After a cold front passes, the air usually cools and clears, although some residual clouds and showers might hang around.",
